article.description: — Ed Croswell had 17 points in Providence's 71-57 victory against Merrimack on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Croswell scores 17, Providence defeats Merrimack 71-57
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- — Ed Croswell had 17 points in Providence's 71-57 victory against Merrimack on Wednesday night. Croswell had seven rebounds for the Friars (4-2). Noah Locke scored 14 points and added seven rebounds. Bryce Hopkins had 13 points. Ziggy Reid led the Warriors (1-5) in scoring, finishing with 21 points. Javon Bennett added 11 points and four steals for Merrimack. Mykel Derring finished with eight points. Providence led Merrimack 37-26 at the half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
